[{"id":"VR865044","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">What is the mass of the rod?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR865044_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A thin rod of length <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"L\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"L\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>L</mi></math></span></span> and mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"M\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"M\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>M</mi></math></span></span> is placed on a horizontal table pivoted about an axle through its center. The rotational inertia of the rod about its center is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"one twelfth M L squared\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"one twelfth M L squared\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>12</mn></mfrac><mi>M</mi><msup><mi>L</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math></span></span>. A spring with spring constant <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"k\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"k\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>k</mi></math></span></span> is fixed to a point on the table and perpendicularly to one end of the rod. The rod is displaced a small angle <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"theta\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>θ</mi></math></span></span> from equilibrium and released, as shown in the Top View figure. The rod oscillates in simple harmonic motion with period <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"T\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"T\" overflow=\"scroll\"> <mi>T</mi> </math></span></span>.</p>\n\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a top view of a rod that pivots about an axle through its center. The mass of the rod is M and the distance from the axle to one end of the rod is one half L. One end of the rod is attached perpendicularly to a spring with spring constant k, and the rod is pivoted by an angle theta from equilibrium.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR865044.g01.svg\" /></div>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"one fourth times the fraction with numerator K T squared, and denominator pi squared\"><math alttext=\"one fourth times the fraction with numerator K T squared, and denominator pi squared\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mfrac><mrow><mi>k</mi><msup><mi>T</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><msup><mi>π</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"three fourths times the fraction with numerator k T squared, and denominator pi squared\"><math alttext=\"three fourths times the fraction with numerator k T squared, and denominator pi squared\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mfrac><mrow><mi>k</mi><msup><mi>T</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><msup><mi>π</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"three halves times the fraction with numerator k T squared, and denominator pi squared\"><math alttext=\"three halves times the fraction with numerator k T squared, and denominator pi squared\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfrac><mrow><mi>k</mi><msup><mi>T</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><msup><mi>π</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3 times the fraction with numerator k T squared, and denominator pi squared\"><math alttext=\"3 times the fraction with numerator k T squared, and denominator pi squared\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mn>3</mn><mfrac><mrow><mi>k</mi><msup><mi>T</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><msup><mi>π</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></mstyle></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":1}]